info.name: Petfinder
info.description:
This is a sample test automation suite using Postman. Each subdirectory will have its own folder, and each subdirectory will have child folders that represent specific endpoints (such as /animals, /types, etc).

The purpose of this repo is to:

- Explore different types of test assertions possible with Postman
- Efficient uses of global, environment, collection and local variables
- Schema validation strategies that help detect discrepancies in data types and response structure

item.name: authentication

exec: pm.test("access_token is returned with valid client_id and secret for grant_type === client_credentials", function () {

item.description: All Petfinder routes require an access_token, which can be obtained via POST /v2/oauth2/token with valid credentials. The credentials are stored in an "Environments" file, which will not be included in this repository for security reasons.
